{
	"info": {
		"name": "Eurobase Email & Password Reset",
		"description": "Tests for transactional email endpoints: platform forgot/reset password, end-user forgot/reset password, email verification, resend verification, email templates, and email status.\n\nRun tests in order — later tests depend on variables set by earlier ones.\n\n## Setup\n\n1. `make setup` — start Postgres, Redis, MinIO\n2. Apply migrations including 000015: `source .env.local && migrate -path migrations -database \"$DATABASE_URL\" up`\n3. Start gateway: `source .env.local && go run ./cmd/gateway/`\n4. Select the \"Eurobase Local\" environment in Postman\n5. Run \"Phase 0 — Platform Auth\" from the auth-tests collection first to set `platform_token` and `project_id`\n\n## Note on email delivery\n\nWithout `SCW_TEM_SECRET_KEY` set, the gateway logs email content instead of sending. Check gateway stdout for logged emails including tokens. You can extract tokens from logs to test reset/verify flows end-to-end.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"variable": [],
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Phase 1 — Email Status",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "E1.1 Get Email Status",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
									"pm.test('Has configured field', () => {",
									"    const json = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('configured');",
									"    pm.expect(typeof json.configured).to.eql('boolean');",
									"    pm.environment.set('email_configured', json.configured);",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{platform_token}}" }
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/platform/config/email-status",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["platform", "config", "email-status"]
						}
					}
				}
			]
		},
